Completed slice:
- 2026-05-13: Completed CLDR compiled-table slice and official `cldr-json` fetch path correction.

Implementation decisions:
- CLDR fetch defaults to `https://github.com/unicode-org/cldr-json` and uses sparse checkout for only required files.
- Supported upstream paths are `cldr-json/cldr-core/supplemental/plurals.json`, `cldr-json/cldr-numbers-full/main/{locale}/numbers.json`, and `cldr-json/cldr-dates-full/main/{locale}/ca-gregorian.json`.
- Local staged CLDR import remains for tests and offline development, but it expects the same `cldr-json/...` subtree shape.
- Runtime CLDR production lookup lives in typed tables under `crates/linguini-cldr/src/data/compiled.rs`; JSON loaders are ingestion/cache-only.
- CLDR Rust source generation moved to proc-macro crate `linguini-cldr-macros`, using `syn` for macro input parsing and `quote` for compile errors.
- `crates/linguini-cldr/src/data.rs` was split into `data/` modules and cache tests were moved to keep source files below the hard file-size limit.
- Near-limit source files remain split-required before future growth: `crates/linguini-syntax/src/lib.rs`, `crates/linguini-syntax/src/lexer.rs`, and `crates/linguini-syntax/src/parser/locale_parser.rs`.

